  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\n`verify-contract` does not check that the contract path argument is within the project's configured `src` directory. If the contract is outside that directory, it will fail with a misleading error.\r\n\r\nMisleading error\r\n```\r\nError: \r\n   0: Failed to get standard json input: cannot resolve file at \"\"/path/to/actual/contract/location/Contract.sol\"\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nInstead, `verify_contract` should check that the path has the project `src` dir as a prefix, and inform the user if it is outside\r\n\r\nDesired behavior:\r\n```\r\nError:\r\n   0: Contract \"/path/to/actual/contract/location/Contract.sol\" is outside of project source directory \"/path/to/foundry/expected/src/\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nNote that the doubled `\"\"...\"\"` is due to escaped quotes in the underlying ethers-solc error message :)\r\n\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
